-- Circuit City posts quarterly loss
-- 
-- Wed Apr 4, 2007 8:18am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/04/businesspro-circuitcity-results-dc-idUSWEN610320070404

 

 ATLANTA  (Reuters) - Consumer electronics retailer Circuit 
City Stores Inc. CC.N reported a fourth-quarter loss on 
Wednesday as it took charges to close stores and had weaker 
sales at stores open at least a year. 

  The loss was $12.2 million, or 7 cents a share, for the 
fourth quarter ended February 28, compared with a profit of 
$141.4 million, or 82 cents a share, a year earlier.  The latest results included $144.6 million in pretax 
charges.